translated: JÄBNBOBG, Axel, Engineer, Oskarshamn, son of Linde's worker, unmarried, born in 1888 to Johannes Carlsson and Carin Andersson, married to Olga Nilsson. Studied at Ing.Akademie Wismar (mechanical engineering) in 1914. Employed at a mechanical workshop in Riga in 1914, ASEA 1915-1918, assistant director at AB Gas, Water and Heat in Stockholm from 1919 to 1922, owner since 1923 of Järnborg's mechanical workshop and pipeline business in Oskarshamn with branches in Kalmar and Karlskrona. Participated in municipal committees and boards.

structured.description: Axel JÄBNBOBG was born in Oskarshamn in 1888. He studied mechanical engineering at Ing.Akademie Wismar in 1914. He worked at a mechanical workshop in Riga in 1914, then at ASEA from 1915 to 1918. From 1919 to 1922, he served as an Assistant Director at AB Gas, Water and Heat in Stockholm. In 1923, he became the owner of Järnborg's Mechanical Workshop and Pipeline Business in Oskarshamn, which had branches in Kalmar and Karlskrona. Axel JÄBNBOBG actively participated in municipal committees and boards.
